I"E<p><strong>The LED Globe</strong> was a large semicircular arc <em>(1.5m diameter)</em> lined with RGB LEDs. By rotating at a high speed about a vertical axis, it could display images mid-air, like a hologram.</p>

<figure class="half ">
  
    
      <a href="/assets/images/projects/globe_leds.jpg">
          <img src="/assets/images/projects/globe_leds.jpg" alt="placeholder image 1" />
      </a>
    
  
    
      <a href="/assets/images/projects/globe_earth_rmv.jpeg">
          <img src="/assets/images/projects/globe_earth_rmv.jpeg" alt="placeholder image 2" />
      </a>
    
  
  
</figure>

<p>Each image was split into vertical segments, that were sent to the LEDs in a timed manner as the arc rotated. With a sufficient speed of rotation, the whole image appears mid-air, due to persistance of vision.</p>

<figure class="third ">
  
    
      <a href="/assets/images/projects/globe_avengers.png">
